2082456,http://www.dailymile.com/entries/2082456,2010-06-09 04:00:00,Hogtown Creek Greenway,alright,00:00:00,1.0000,1.6000,"Ran by myself so I could work on form.  I had to try out my new RunAmocs!  I like them a lot.  Seems like they are a little bit small (my toes end up pushing on the front inside of the moccasin) even though the Soft Star web site says to go smaller if between sizes (I wear size 9 1/2, ordered size 9).  The longest part of the shoe seems too close to the middle of the shoe, rather than offset in front of the big toe.  Also, the top of the shoe stretches over the big toe like a tent (as if there is not enough internal height). Not sure if a larger size would fix these issues or maybe just have to run in them more than once.",,RunAmoc,,110,59:59:59,59:59:59

She actually had a nice midfoot strike, even though she was wearing marshmallow shoes.  I hung in behind them for a while, and when I turned onto 8th Ave I just started cruising (the other runners had stopped to rest)... and kept cruising... and kept cruising. I had some free time today for a second run, decided to go exploring since I have never run there before.  There are no facilities despite what is shown on the map.  Had a nice strong breeze the whole time bringing in cloud cover. I think it would have been hot and miserable otherwise. The trails are nice and wide (and flat), this might make a good location for a group trail run. There is of course some sugar sand but really not bad, most trails are covered in leaves or pine needles or planted in grass. The Yellow loop is a convenient 5k. Taking a map along was very helpful, I would have had trouble without it.  Wore my NB MT00 sockless, had no issues.  Lesson of the day: Top of your water bottle when you get the chance.  I drank some of mine on the way there and didn't refill from my jug before leaving my car.",2,New Balance Minimus Trail Zero,,1288,00:11:07.021277,00:06:55.231788

15162562,http://www.dailymile.com/entries/15162562,2012-05-18 02:24:36,long tempo run,good,00:56:00,7.5000,12.1000,"Trying to correct some of my minor form issues that I noticed in the high speed video I received from the UF Ortho study.  The two big things were 1. I had asymmetric arm carriage 2. I had completely lost the ""falling forward"" pattern. I noticed while running tonight that falling forward encourages ""popping"" the feet back up off the ground more quickly. I remember that! But I had not been doing it. I wore my Altra Sampsons for the first time in a while. I think my previous Achilles complaints from these shoes stemmed from the fact that I was doing it wrong. Better form = no pains. It also means faster pace with less effort.",3,Altra Sampson,,693,00:07:28,00:04:37.68595

23087435,http://www.dailymile.com/entries/23087435,2013-06-02 21:28:18,All over San Felasco,good,04:52:00,25.5000,41.1000,"A long day of trail running at San Felasco in the heat wearing my Merrell Vapor Gloves. I started the morning by exploring the hiking trails on the south side of Millhopper Road. Then I followed blue blaze trail to a service road, crossed the gate into the wilderness area, and ended up on horse trails on the north side of the park. Lots of mountain bikes out today. I wandered on curvy singletrack to the north parking area to refill my water bottles and cool down. I was hot and tired by this point (3 hours in and approaching noon), so I wanted to avoid the singletrack on the way back. I needed to get to the bridges near the Soggy Bottom / CreekSide loops to hop back on the horse trails and find that gate. Never did find my way. Next time I will take a map. After getting lost, using up all my food and gels, and almost running out of water, I decided to cross the wilderness swamp that I had used in years past (follow the powerlines). I didn't need to wade through anything more than ankle-deep water (whew!). I did a lot walking during that last hour. I was glad to arrive back at my car with cold water and food waiting for me. Today was a nice adventure (despite the biting flies and ticks), and I saw a couple of hawks, a big wise old owl, some deer (including a cute little fawn), and a large herd of feral pigs. Love the Vapor Gloves.",4,Merrell Vapor Glove red,hot sunny,3541,00:11:27.058824,00:07:06.277372

25302774,http://www.dailymile.com/entries/25302774,2013-09-28 19:02:46,San Felasco trails LONG run,good,05:37:00,29.5000,47.5000,"I was getting ready for my LONG run this morning when I turned around to find my youngest daughter sitting there in her running clothes. She said ""I want to run with you!"" How could I say ""no"" to that?  We ran around our neighborhood together in the dark for a little bit before I sat her down with breakfast and then I finished packing up to hit the trails of San Felasco. I ran from the south side hiking trails to the north side horse trails. I explored some of the mountain bike trails such as ""Hidden Rise"". I only saw two groups of riders and otherwise had the north side trails to myself. I am kind of estimating pace and distance, but this was definitely my lifetime longest run ever!   Weather was nice with a breeze and light mist much of the morning. Nature today included a snake that I almost stepped on, I think it was a cottonmouth!
